text.section:
The brief description shall include:
the title or type or plan of policy, including the term "industrial" or "wholesale" if applicable;
how long premiums are to be paid;
if and when the premium may change, except for a change because of a supplementary agreement;
if the benefit is not level, the use of the term "graded benefit" or a similar term to so indicate;
whether the policy is participating or nonparticipating;
if the policy is written on a rated underwriting basis, the terms "substandard class" or "rated class" or a substantially similar term; and
if the policy provides for the return of premiums as an additional benefit, the period during which the benefit is applicable.
